text: Machu Qichqa (Quechua machu old, old person, Chanka Quechua qichqa cliff,Diccionario Bilingüe Quechua Castellano, Cusco Collao y Ayacucho-Chanka, see Risco "old cliff", also spelled Machoccechcca) is a mountain in the Huancavelica Region in Peru, about high. It is situated in the Huaytará Province, Pilpichaca District. Machu Qichqa lies southwest of Yawarqucha and northwest of Wakan Q'allay. == References == Category:Mountains of Peru Category:Mountains of Huancavelica Region
